  <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Process_Description">Process Description</span></h2>
  <p>A key change between ITIL V2 and ITIL V3 has been a new focus on continually improving services and processes. ITIL V3 introduced specific processes for service and process evaluation and <a class="mw-selflink selflink">improvement</a>. </p>
  <p>In <i><b>ITIL 2011</b></i>, the <i>CSI Register</i> has been introduced as a central document or database where all improvement opportunities and initiatives are recorded. As a result, one of the main outputs from CSI now is the CSI Register - instead of the <i>Service Improvement Plan (SIP)</i> as per ITIL V3 (2007). SIPs now take a much less prominent role as in ITIL 2007 (SIPs may still be used as plans to implement improvements to individual services or processes). </p>
  <p>To reflect the new structure of Service Strategy processes in ITIL 2011 the interfaces of the process have been adapted. The process overview of <a href="/images/itilcsithree.jpg" target="_blank" title="Itil-definition-csi-initiatives.jpg">ITIL Definition of CSI Initiatives (.JPG)</a> shows the key information flows. </p>
  <p>&#160;</p>
